{"type":"entity","name":"CyclicWorkflowsPattern","entityType":"Pattern","observations":["Concept: Creating feedback loops where work is revised.","Implementation: Use standard AddEdge(source, target) where target eventually points back to source.","Constraint: The framework does not automatically detect infinite loops.","Best Practice: Implement a \"Loop Controller\" or iteration counter within one of the agents (e.g., ReviewerAgent) to force termination after N cycles."]}
{"type":"entity","name":"TypeAdaptationPattern","entityType":"Pattern","observations":["Problem: In a loop A -> B -> A, if A expects input type X but B returns type Y, the cycle breaks.","Solution: Introduce an AdapterAgent (B -> Adapter -> A) to convert Y to X.","Example: Demo 3 used FeedbackAdapterAgent to convert (string, string) tuple from Reviewer back to string for Writer."]}
{"type":"entity","name":"StatefulExecutorsPattern","entityType":"Pattern","observations":["Concept: Executors are instantiated once and reused.","Implementation: Use private fields (e.g., _revisionCount) to track state across multiple invocations in a workflow."]}
